00:05:37.857 --> 00:05:41.142
That is it.

00:05:41.142 --> 00:05:44.428
Five minutes.

00:05:44.428 --> 00:05:47.714
Three bullet points.

00:05:47.714 --> 00:05:51.000
The magic of this approach is that most of the time, you will not stop after five minutes.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.285
Because once your brain is engaged in the material, continuing feels easier than stopping.

00:05:54.285 --> 00:05:57.571
Your brain has already overcome the hardest part: the beginning.

00:05:57.571 --> 00:06:00.857
But even if you do stop after five minutes, you have succeeded.

00:06:00.857 --> 00:06:04.142
You studied for five minutes more than you would have otherwise.

00:06:04.142 --> 00:06:07.428
And tomorrow, starting again will be significantly easier because your brain remembers that this task was manageable.

00:06:07.428 --> 00:06:10.714
Each small session builds a pattern.

00:06:10.714 --> 00:06:13.999
And patterns create habits.

00:06:13.999 --> 00:06:17.999
Here is something most students get wrong.

00:06:17.999 --> 00:06:21.999
Reading is not studying.

00:06:21.999 --> 00:06:25.999
Highlighting is not studying.

00:06:25.999 --> 00:06:29.999
Re-reading your notes is not studying.

00:06:29.999 --> 00:06:33.999
Your brain needs to actively work with information to remember it.

00:06:33.999 --> 00:06:37.999
This is called active recall, and it is one of the most effective learning techniques ever studied.

00:06:37.999 --> 00:06:41.999
After you have gone through one explanation from TeraAI, ask: "Ask me five simple questions to check if I understood the explanation."

TeraAI will ask you questions one by one.

00:06:41.999 --> 00:06:45.999
